                  <summary><title>Ulakanīti</title> (literally "The right conduct in the world") by Ulakanātar (17th c. at the latest) is a didactic work containing aphorisms on good conduct in the form of don'ts. The present version consists in ten numbered sections of eight lines each.</summary>
                  
